{
  "text": "Associated costs for event-specific medical utilization were estimated from published literature. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Statewide aspirin use campaign costs were measured on a per person-year basis using aggregate, projected annual campaign expenses divided by the total target population from the Hibbing study. Average campaign costs were estimated at $6.75 per personyear. Furthermore, the campaign was assumed to run for 3 years only. All costs were inflation-adjusted to 2012 dollars using the Minnesota medical consumer price index.",
